[[entries]]
name = "v56x_features"
description = "v5.6.x feature additions — preprocessor, attributes, overflow operators, IR optimization arc"
category = "cyrius"
---
=== PREPROCESSOR EXTENSIONS (v5.6.1) ===

#else / #elif / #ifndef now work alongside the existing #ifdef / #endif:

    #ifdef CYRIUS_TARGET_LINUX
        var fd = file_open("/proc/self/exe", 0);
    #elif CYRIUS_TARGET_WIN
        var fd = win_get_image_handle();
    #else
        # macOS / other platforms fall here
    #endif

    #ifndef CYRIUS_BAREMETAL
        println("running on hosted platform");
    #endif

State machine is per nesting level (4-state encoding stored at heap
0x97F10): EMITTING / SEARCHING / DONE / OUTER_SKIP. `#elif` after a
taken `#ifdef` branch is correctly skipped; nested blocks inside a
parent's skip path don't re-trigger emit.

Closes the long-standing v5.4.x gap where paired `#ifdef` was the only
way to branch. The 60+ stdlib paired-`#ifdef` sites can migrate to the
cleaner form at leisure — no breaking change.

=== EXPLICIT OVERFLOW OPERATORS (v5.6.2) ===

9 new tokens make integer-overflow intent visible at the call site:

    +%  -%  *%      # wrapping (alias for bare + - *; 2's complement wrap)
    +|  -|  *|      # saturating (clamp to i64::MIN / i64::MAX)
    +?  -?  *?      # checked (panic on overflow with exit code 57)

Wrapping ops are bytes-identical to the bare operator — they document
intent, no runtime cost. Saturating and checked variants compile to
calls into lib/overflow.cyr helpers (`_sat_add_i64`, `_sat_sub_i64`,
`_sat_mul_i64`, `_chk_add_i64`, `_chk_sub_i64`, `_chk_mul_i64`).

Checked-panic uses `syscall(60, 57)`. Exit code 57 is reserved to
distinguish overflow panics from POSIX signal exits and from
assert-summary returns. Production / kernel code should prefer
explicit wrapping + range guards over `+?` for hot paths; `+?` is
intended for boundary checks where overflow is genuinely a bug.

=== ATTRIBUTES — #must_use, @unsafe, #deprecated (v5.6.3 + v5.6.4) ===

Function-level attributes flag intent at declaration; the compiler
warns at call sites or compile time. All three are stored in a 4-bit
mask in fn_flags[fi] at heap 0xFC000.

#must_use (v5.6.3, bit 0):
    #must_use
    fn checked_op(x): i64 { return x * 2; }

    fn main() {
        checked_op(21);          # warning: result of #must_use fn discarded
        var r = checked_op(21);  # OK
        return checked_op(21);   # OK
    }

The diagnostic fires only at expression-statement discard (`fn();`).
Assignment, `return fn();`, arg-passing, and conditional sites
(`if (fn())`) are unaffected. Method-call discards are deferred for
future patch.

@unsafe (v5.6.3, bit 1 reserved; block-form keyword token 123):
    @unsafe {
        store64(some_raw_ptr, 0);
        var x = load64(some_other_raw_ptr);
    }

Advisory only — no runtime cost. Nested `@unsafe` blocks emit a
stylistic warning ("nested unsafe is redundant") but compile.

#deprecated (v5.6.4, bit 2; required string argument):
    #deprecated("use sha256_init() — sha1 is collision-broken")
    fn sha1_init() { ... }

Warns at every call site (unlike #must_use's discard-only). The
required string lives in fn_deprecated_msg at heap 0x104000 (4096 ×
8 B token offsets). Useful for ecosystem-wide migration: ship the
deprecated marker in version N, give consumers one or two minor
versions of warning, remove in version N+2.

=== IR OPTIMIZATION ARC (v5.6.5 — v5.6.27) ===

The v5.6.x minor is the **compiler optimization arc**. Six phases
labelled O1 through O6:

  O1 (v5.6.5):    FNV-1a FINDFN hash + CYRIUS_PROF baseline
  O2 (v5.6.7-11): post-emit codebuf peephole — 5 categories
                  • cat 1: `x * 2^n → shl/lsl` strength reduction
                  • cat 2: ECONDCMP → `test rax, rax` flag-reuse
                            (BIGGEST WIN: -21,856 B / -4.15 %)
                  • cat 3: redundant push/pop cancel (CP rewind)
                  • cat 4: commutative shuttle elim x86 (-16,960 B)
                  • cat 5: commutative shuttle elim aarch64
                            (closes O2; native aarch64 cc5 -17,672 B)
  O3 (v5.6.12-18, ✅ closed):
                  • O3a (v5.6.12-15): IR instrumentation + correctness
                    audit — IR_RAW_EMIT markers in 15 parse_*.cyr
                    direct-emit blocks; LASE bug found and fixed
                    (parse_ctrl.cyr loop_top IR_NOP landing pads);
                    ESETCC IR-emit-order inversion fixed (record IR
                    AFTER sub-emit)
                  • O3b (v5.6.16): IR-level constant fold (130 folds /
                    774 B NOP-fill at IR=3 on cc5 self-compile)
                  • O3b-fix (v5.6.17): bitmap liveness + DCE — fixed
                    via CYRIUS_DCE_CAP bisection methodology
                    (IR_RAX_CLOBBER reads RCX, not writes; same for
                    IR_ADD_IMM_X1 + IR_RAW_EMIT). 678 kills /
                    2,010 B NOP-fill at IR=3.
                  • O3c (v5.6.18): dead-store elimination + fixed-
                    point driver. 15 DSE / 6,099 B NOP-fill at IR=3
                    in 3 fixpoint iterations (cascade caught 3 more
                    folds 132→135). Copy-prop deferred long-term
                    (recon: 0 B direct savings on stack-machine IR).
  O4 (v5.6.19-24, ✅ closed): linear-scan register allocation.
                  • O4a (v5.6.19): per-fn live-interval infrastructure
                  • O4b (v5.6.20): Poletto-Sarkar picker
                  • O4c (v5.6.22): auto-enable infra (DISABLED) +
                    picker correctness fix (loop-back time-share)
                  • v5.6.23: misdiagnosis correction —
                    asm/regalloc layout collision (body-scan token 48)
                  • v5.6.24: **default-on flip** + SysV ECALLPOPS
                    r12-r14 clobber fix (codegen-scratch-must-be-
                    caller-saved rule). cc5 +20,304 B for save/
                    restore overhead.
  O5 (dropped): maximal-munch instruction selection. Recon found
                    0 fused-op candidates (cyrius's stack-machine IR
                    keeps a push between sub-expression results and
                    consumers); push-imm rewrite has rax-side-effect
                    + forward-jump-target issues. Pinned long-term —
                    needs an IR-level push-elision pass first. v5.6.26
                    shipped peephole refinement + doc completion in
                    place of the original O5 scope.
  O6 (v5.6.27, pinned): codebuf compaction (NOP harvest with
                            jump+fixup repair) — REAL binary shrinkage,
                            sweeps accumulated NOP-fill from O3 passes
                            (~6,099 B at IR=3) plus picker patches
                            (~16 KB at default-on cc5)

Late-arc bonus shrinkage:
  v5.6.25: aarch64 EPOPARG push/pop-cancel completion (closed v5.6.11
           mirror gap; native aarch64 cc5 −20,368 B / −3.94 %)

=== IR PIPELINE ENV VARS ===

CYRIUS_IR=1     Record IR while emitting x86 (no optimization passes)
CYRIUS_IR=2     Verbose IR dump (incl. ir_dump per fn)
CYRIUS_IR=3     Record IR + run apply_lase + ir_const_fold + ir_dce
                (the optimization mode; 3-step b==c required)

CYRIUS_DCE_CAP=N
                Cap DCE kills at first N candidates. -1 = uncapped
                (default at IR=3). Set to a small value to bisect
                wrongly-killed nodes during future IR-pass debug
                (v5.6.17 bisection methodology — saved as a load-
                bearing knob; same pattern saved cycles at v5.6.22
                regalloc time-share bug + v5.6.24 ECALLPOPS bug).

CYRIUS_REGALLOC_AUTO_CAP=N
                (v5.6.22 infra, default-on at v5.6.24) Cap auto-
                regalloc at first N x86 fns (no inline asm). Default
                = uncapped. Set 0 to disable; positive N for bisection.

CYRIUS_REGALLOC_DUMP=1
                (v5.6.19) Print per-fn live intervals to stderr.

CYRIUS_REGALLOC_PICKER_CAP=N
                (v5.6.20) Cap picker assignments per fn. Bisection knob.

CYRIUS_PROF=1   (v5.6.5; cross-platform v5.6.6) Wall-clock total
                compile time via clock_gettime (Linux syscall 228
                / aarch64 113 / kernel32!GetTickCount64 on PE /
                libSystem._clock_gettime_nsec_np on Mach-O via
                __got[6]).

=== BYTE-IDENTITY GATE EXPANSION ===

Since v5.6.16, the 3-step fixpoint must hold at BOTH IR_ENABLED=0
AND IR_ENABLED=3. Two distinct invariants:

  IR=0:  cc5_a (built from main.cyr at IR=0) compiles main.cyr to
         cc5_b. cc5_b compiles main.cyr to cc5_c. b == c.

  IR=3:  cc5_a compiled with CYRIUS_IR=3 produces cc5_b (with
         optimization-pass NOP-fill applied). cc5_b run with
         CYRIUS_IR=3 produces cc5_c. b == c.

The IR=0 and IR=3 outputs DIFFER from each other (NOPs in place of
optimized-out instructions), but each is internally self-consistent.
Real binary shrinkage waits for v5.6.22 codebuf compaction.

=== STATE-DOC SPLIT (v5.6.16) ===

CLAUDE.md is now preferences/process/procedures only. Volatile state
(version, cc5 size, in-flight slots, recent shipped releases,
consumers, verification hosts) lives in docs/development/state.md.
Per-release narrative lives in docs/development/completed-phases.md.
The architecture doc (docs/architecture/cyrius.md) is the durable
"how / why" — design decisions that change rarely.

This split catches the rot pattern where every release was appending
a sentence to CLAUDE.md's "Current State" paragraph until it became
unmaintainable. The pattern generalizes: durable rules in the
top-level instruction file; volatile state in a refreshed-per-
release sibling doc.

=== POST-OPTIMIZATION-ARC PATCHES (v5.6.28 — v5.6.43) ===

After the O1-O6 arc closed at v5.6.27, the rest of v5.6.x
ran correctness fixes, dep bumps, and heap reshuffles. The
significant ones:

  v5.6.30 (preprocessor):  PP_DERIVE_* `src_base` fix —
                            PP_IFDEF_PASS reads past 524288 B
                            input_buf cap returned stale heap;
                            v5.6.42 closed the rest of the
                            same-class family (PP_HASH /
                            PP_DEFINE / PP_DEFINED / PP_GETVAL /
                            PP_EVAL_IF).
  v5.6.31 (PE/Win11):      HIGH_ENTROPY_VA SIGSEGV — EREAD_PE/
                            EWRITE_PE used `mov rax, [rsp+0x28]`
                            for kernel-written DWORD, picking up
                            4 B of stack garbage. Fix: 32-bit
                            `mov eax` (auto-zero-extends).
                            HIGH_ENTROPY_VA enabled by default.
  v5.6.32 (aarch64 native): missing `include "src/common/ir.cyr"`
                            in main_aarch64_native.cyr (latent
                            since v5.6.12 O3a). Earlier
                            "macOS drift" framing was wrong.
  v5.6.33 / v5.6.36:       Mach-O / Win11 PE gate fixture
                            rewrites. Both pinned as "platform
                            drift" but were `fn main() { ... }`
                            fixtures that never ran main()
                            (cyrius has no auto-call). See
                            `feedback_verify_slot_premise_first`.
  v5.6.34:                 stdlib `alloc` grow-undersize SIGSEGV —
                            lib/alloc.cyr grew by fixed 0x100000
                            regardless of size; alloc(>1MB) near
                            boundary SIGSEGV'd. Fix: round to
                            1 MB grain on Linux; loop on macOS.
  v5.6.35:                 sankoch 2.0.1 → 2.0.3 dep pin (sit
                            symptom 2 closed via sankoch's deflate
                            encoder fix; cyrius itself unchanged).
  v5.6.37:                 SSL_connect deadlock — libssl routed
                            through fdlopen instead of dynlib_open
                            so libssl gets a real glibc TCB.
                            BREAKING: tls.cyr consumers must
                            include fdlopen.cyr first (PP cap
                            blocks auto-include).
  v5.6.38:                 .so emission slot premise check —
                            removed dead SYSV_HASH (14 LOC).
                            Third consecutive premise-disprove
                            slot.
  v5.6.39:                 cc5 --version drift fix — version
                            string drifted from 5.6.29-1 across
                            9 releases because version-bump.sh's
                            regex didn't match `-N` hotfix
                            suffix. Fix: removed hardcoded
                            literals; src/version_str.cyr is
                            auto-generated from VERSION.
  v5.6.40:                 lib/tls.cyr ALPN/mTLS hook surface —
                            tls_dlsym + tls_connect_with_ctx_hook.
                            Sandhi-blocking. + patra 1.6.0 →
                            1.8.3 + preprocess_out 1 MB → 2 MB
                            heap reshuffle.
  v5.6.41:                 SysV 16-byte stack alignment fix for
                            odd-stack-arg callers. ECALLPOPS's
                            `add rsp, 48` left rsp 8-aligned at
                            CALL when nextra was odd; downstream
                            libssl SSE-using prologs SIGSEGV'd.
                            See field_notes/compiler.toml for
                            the calling-convention math.
  v5.6.42:                 PP_DEFINE/DEFINED `src_base` hardening
                            (closes v5.6.30 same-class) +
                            heap-map fix-through (stale
                            `0xA0000 fixup_tbl` docs in 4 main
                            files; v5.6.27 had repurposed the
                            region 16 patches ago).
  v5.6.43:                 v5.6.x closeout — sigil 2.9.0 → 2.9.3
                            + sankoch 2.0.3 → 2.1.0 + output_buf
                            1 MB → 2 MB heap reshuffle (16
                            regions shifted +1 MB; brk 22.5 →
                            23.5 MB). Last patch of v5.6.x.

=== v5.6.x CLOSING METRICS ===

  Date range:           2026-04-13 → 2026-04-25 (12 days)
  Patch count:          44 (v5.6.0 through v5.6.43)
  cc5 size delta:       508,880 → 531,888 B (+23,008 B / +4.5 %)
                         Tradeoff: regalloc save/restore
                         overhead + alignment branches outweigh
                         peephole shrinkage at IR=0.
  Native aarch64 cc5:   471,360 → 463,768 B (−7,592 B / −1.6 %).
  check.sh gates:       22 → 26 (preprocessor_past_cap +
                         sysv_odd_stack_args + regression-tls-live
                         + regression-macho-cross-build).
  .tcyr files:          84 → 87.
  Deps refreshed:       patra 1.6.0 → 1.8.3, sigil 2.9.0 → 2.9.3,
                         sankoch 2.0.1 → 2.1.0.
  Heap brk:             0x150B000 (21 MB) → 0x178B000 (23.5 MB).

  Optimization arc landed: O1 / O2(5/5) / O3(a-c) / O4(a-c).
  Optimization arc dropped: O5 (maximal-munch — recon found
                             zero fused-op candidates on cyrius's
                             stack-machine IR; pinned long-term).
                            O6 landed at v5.6.27 (codebuf
                             compaction; −11,536 B / −2.13 %).

